p.5: The effects were assessed not only by the criteria of nuclear and cytoplasmic steady-state levels of RanGTP; we also considered that transport at the expense of the Ran gradient depletes the nuclear RanGTP pool. Therefore, it is an important criterion which level of work load or `exercise' the system can sustain. This number reflects the maximum rate of nuclear RanGTP production (in mM/sec), and we refer to it here as the dynamic capacity for Ran-driven transport.
